cor_long <- as.data.frame(as.table(bfi_cor))
names(cor_long) <- c("var1","var2","r")

ggplot(cor_long, aes(var1, var2, fill = r)) +
  geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_gradient2(limits = c(-1,1), low = "firebrick", mid = "white", high = "steelblue") +
  labs(title = "BFI Item Correlations", x = NULL, y = NULL, fill = "r") +

0.8 7) SAT & ACT: Grouped Summaries

Goal: Create a binned summary of SATV (e.g., cut into quantiles) and compute mean ACT per bin. Plot as a column chart with 95% CIs.

sat2 <- sat %>%
  mutate(SATV_bin = cut_number(SATV, n = 6)) %>%
  group_by(SATV_bin) %>%
  summarise(
    mean_ACT = mean(ACT, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_ACT   = sd(ACT, na.rm = TRUE),
    n        = n(),
    se       = sd_ACT/sqrt(n),
    lower    = mean_ACT - 1.96*se,
    upper    = mean_ACT + 1.96*se,
    .groups = "drop"
  )

ggplot(sat2, aes(SATV_bin, mean_ACT)) +
  geom_col(fill = "steelblue") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), width = .2) +
  labs(title = "Mean ACT by SATV Bin (95% CIs)", x = "SATV bin", y = "Mean ACT") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13)

0.11 10) Ability: Correlation Heatmap (from Covariance)

Data: psych::ability.cov (list with $cov and test names)
Goal: Convert covariance to correlation with cov2cor(), then plot a correlation heatmap. Highlight clusters (e.g., spatial, verbal).

data(ability.cov)

R_ability <- cov2cor(ability.cov$cov)

corrplot(R_ability, method = "color", order = "hclust", addrect = 3,
         tl.col = "black", tl.cex = .8,
         col = colorRampPalette(c("darkred","white","steelblue"))(200),
         title = "Ability Test Correlations")

0.12 11) Harman74: Correlogram with Numbers

Data: psych::Harman74.cor (correlation matrix + N)
Goal: Plot a mixed correlogram: symbols/colors on one triangle and numbers on the other.

data(Harman74.cor)

R_harman <- Harman74.cor$cov  # actually a correlation matrix
# Upper triangle: circles; Lower: numbers
corrplot(R_harman, method = "circle", type = "upper", order = "hclust",
         tl.col = "black", tl.cex = .6)
corrplot(R_harman, method = "number", type = "lower", add = TRUE, diag = FALSE, number.cex = .5)

0.13 12) BFI: Trait Profiles by Education

Goal: Compute mean E, A, C, N, O per participant, pivot long to trait/value.
Create a profile plot (trait on x, mean value on y) by education (facet or color). Add CIs.

bfi_traits <- bfi %>%
  mutate(
    E = rowMeans(select(., E1:E5), na.rm = TRUE),
    A = rowMeans(select(., A1:A5), na.rm = TRUE),
    C = rowMeans(select(., C1:C5), na.rm = TRUE),
    N = rowMeans(select(., N1:N5), na.rm = TRUE),
    O = rowMeans(select(., O1:O5), na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  select(E,A,C,N,O, education) %>%
  filter(!is.na(education)) %>%
  pivot_longer(E:O, names_to = "Trait", values_to = "Score")

bfi_prof <- bfi_traits %>%
  group_by(education, Trait) %>%
  summarise(
    mean = mean(Score, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd = sd(Score, na.rm = TRUE),
    n = n(),
    se = sd/sqrt(n),
    lower = mean - 1.96*se,
    upper = mean + 1.96*se,
    .groups = "drop"
  )

ggplot(bfi_prof, aes(Trait, mean, group = education, color = factor(education))) +
  geom_line() + geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = lower, ymax = upper), width = .1) +
  labs(title = "Trait Profiles by Education", x = "Trait", y = "Mean (95% CI)", color = "Education") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13)
